      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " الْفَاكِهَةُ مِائَةٌ وَ عِشْرُونَ لَوْناً سَيِّدُهَا الرُّمَّانُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Haroun Bin Muslim, from Mas’ada Bin Ziyad, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The fruits are of one hundred and twenty types, the chief of these being the Pomegranate’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his Harun ibn Muslim from Mas’adah ibn Ziyad who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Fruits are of one hundred twenty colors and the pomegranate is its master.’” "
        ]
      }
